            . I lodge at Jennings'. The prisoner went out with a bag - the prosecutor's wife sent me after him; I overtook him in St. James'-park, and told him to come back - he said he would not; I walked with him till I saw a Policeman, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>JAMES RABITT. I am a Policeman. I took the prisoner, and found the counterpane in the bag.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I brought a counterpane to London, just the colour of this, and happened to put this into the bag with the rest of my things, as I was going into the country; I did not know but it was my own, as my wife was out; my wife gave them the duplicate of some rings to settle it.</p>
